00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:44,198
Not every story in Kerning City is about power. Some are about the things people lose when they run away from home... and the lengths they go to get them back. Alex had left everything behind except the memory of his mother's gold watch... and then the watch was gone too... swallowed by the city's underworld economy, passed from hand to hand until it vanished into a lockpicker's orbit. Mr. Pickall knew where it was. He ALWAYS knew things like that. Getting him to share that knowledge was its own kind of negotiation... carried out in the quiet language of favors and patience that Kerning City runs on.
